    <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to Akansha Grammar High School ("School", "we", "us", or "our"). We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of personal information entrusted to us by students, parents, staff, and visitors.</p>
            <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website, use our management system, or interact with our services. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your personal information.</p>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <strong>Important:</strong> By using our website or services, you consent to the data practices described in this policy. If you do not agree with this policy, please do not access or use our services.
            </div>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect several types of information from and about users of our services:</p>

            <h3>2.1 Student Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details (name, date of birth, gender, address, contact information)</li>
                <li>Parent/guardian information (names, contact details, relationship)</li>
                <li>Academic records (grades, attendance, marks, assignments)</li>
                <li>Health information (allergies, medical conditions, emergency contacts)</li>
                <li>Photographs and videos (for school activities, identification)</li>
                <li>Behavioral records and disciplinary information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Parent/Guardian Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Names and contact details (email, phone, address)</li>
                <li>Occupation and employer information</li>
                <li>Financial information (for fee payments)</li>
                <li>Communication preferences</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.3 Staff Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details (name, address, contact information)</li>
                <li>Employment records (qualifications, work history, performance)</li>
                <li>Attendance and leave records</li>
                <li>Salary and financial information</li>
                <li>Background verification documents</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.4 Website Usage Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>IP address, browser type, and operating system</li>
                <li>Pages visited, time spent on pages, and navigation paths</li>
                <li>Referring website addresses</li>
                <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>

            <h3>3.1 Educational Purposes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Administering admissions and enrollment processes</li>
                <li>Managing academic records and performance tracking</li>
                <li>Recording and reporting attendance</li>
                <li>Facilitating parent-teacher communication</li>
                <li>Organizing school activities, events, and programs</li>
                <li>Providing academic counseling and support services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3.2 Administrative Purposes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Processing fee payments and maintaining financial records</li>
                <li>Managing staff employment and payroll</li>
                <li>Complying with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
                <li>Maintaining school security and safety</li>
                <li>Conducting internal audits and quality assurance</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3.3 Communication Purposes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Sending important notices and updates</li>
                <li>Sharing academic reports and progress updates</li>
                <li>Announcing school events and activities</li>
                <li>Responding to inquiries and support requests</li>
                <li>Conducting surveys and feedback collection</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent personal information to third parties. We may share information only in the following circumstances:</p>

            <h3>4.1 With Consent</h3>
            <p>We may share personal information with your explicit consent, such as publishing student achievements or photographs in school publications or website.</p>

            <h3>4.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
            <p>We may disclose information when required by law, court order, or governmental authority, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of the school, students, staff, or others.</p>

            <h3>4.3 Service Providers</h3>
            <p>We may share information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Payment processing and financial services</li>
                <li>IT support and website hosting</li>
                <li>Transportation services (bus tracking)</li>
                <li>Educational software and platforms</li>
                <li>Background verification services</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These providers are contractually obligated to maintain confidentiality and use the information only for specified purposes.</p>

            <h3>4.4 Educational Authorities</h3>
            <p>We share information with educational boards (CBSE, State Board) and government authorities as required for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Board examination registration</li>
                <li>Transfer certificates and academic records</li>
                <li>Compliance with educational regulations</li>
                <li>Scholarship applications</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encrypted data transmission using SSL/TLS protocols</li>
                <li>Secure password-protected user accounts</li>
                <li>Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
                <li>Access controls limiting data access to authorized personnel</li>
                <li>Regular data backups and disaster recovery procedures</li>
                <li>Staff training on data protection and privacy practices</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <strong>Note:</strong> While we strive to protect your personal information, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
            </div>

            <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected and to comply with legal requirements:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Student Records:</strong> Maintained for the duration of enrollment plus 7 years after graduation/leaving</li>
                <li><strong>Academic Records:</strong> Permanent retention for transcripts; 7 years for other academic documents</li>
                <li><strong>Financial Records:</strong> 7 years from the date of transaction</li>
                <li><strong>Staff Records:</strong> 7 years after termination of employment</li>
                <li><strong>Website Data:</strong> Analytics data retained for 2 years</li>
            </ul>
            <p>After the retention period, we securely delete or anonymize the data unless longer retention is required by law.</p>

            <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>

            <h3>7.1 Access and Correction</h3>
            <p>You may request access to your personal information and request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete data.</p>

            <h3>7.2 Opt-Out</h3>
            <p>You may opt out of receiving promotional communications by following the unsubscribe instructions in emails or contacting us directly. However, we may still send essential administrative communications.</p>

            <h3>7.3 Data Portability</h3>
            <p>You may request a copy of your personal information in a commonly used, machine-readable format.</p>

            <h3>7.4 Withdrawal of Consent</h3>
            <p>Where processing is based on consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time. This will not affect the lawfulness of processing before withdrawal.</p>

            <h3>7.5 Complaints</h3>
            <p>If you have concerns about how we handle your personal information, you may lodge a complaint with us or with the relevant data protection authority.</p>

            <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Our services are intended for educational purposes and involve processing information about minors. We take special precautions to protect children's privacy:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We collect children's information only with parent/guardian consent</li>
                <li>We limit collection to information necessary for educational purposes</li>
                <li>We implement enhanced security measures for children's data</li>
                <li>We do not use children's information for commercial marketing</li>
                <li>Parents/guardians may review, modify, or request deletion of their child's information</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>9. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
            <p>Our website uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance user experience:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality (login sessions, security)</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website</li>
                <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings and preferences</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. However, disabling cookies may affect website functionality.</p>

            <h2>10. Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p>

            <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. We will notify you of any material changes by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Posting the updated policy on our website</li>
                <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
                <li>Sending email notifications for significant changes</li>
                <li>Displaying prominent notices on our website</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.</p>

